<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="iddc91cfa2-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06" identifier="/us/usc/t12/s1831"><num value="1831">§ 1831.</num><heading> Separability of certain provisions of this chapter</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The provisions of this chapter limiting the insurance of the deposits of any depositor to a maximum less than the full amount shall be independent and separable from each and all of the provisions of this chapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="iddc91cfa3-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06">(<ref href="/us/act/1950-09-21/ch967/s2">Sept. 21, 1950, ch. 967, § 2</ref>[23], formerly § 2[21], <ref href="/us/stat/64/894">64 Stat. 894</ref>; renumbered § 2[22], <ref href="/us/pl/90/203/s3">Pub. L. 90–203, § 3</ref>, <date date="1967-12-15">Dec. 15, 1967</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/81/610">81 Stat. 610</ref>; renumbered § 2[23], <ref href="/us/pl/91/508/tI/s101">Pub. L. 91–508, title I, § 101</ref>, <date date="1970-10-26">Oct. 26, 1970</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/84/1114">84 Stat. 1114</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
